page.title: 19Ecology
page.content: {The Walk to Tresham.}We went through fields and valleys. We walked to Alderley and Rose Hill School. After that we started off to go to Tresham. We went up big hills and little hills. We collected many wild flowers and twigs of trees. We got to this big hill and there was corn, it was green. When we could see Tresham we all ran up to be the first. We delivered questionnaires to all the houses there. We walked back through the fields along part of the Cotswold Way. There were sheep watching us go by. There were muddy bits and I got stuck in the mud. Some of the crops we saw were barley, maize, wheat and grass. Some trees were sycamore, elder, ash, horse chestnut, maple, hawthorn, oak, beech, silver birch, lime, yew, and larch.
